# Hold 60fps

Target: a locked 60fps (16.6ms frame) on a mid-tier 2023 laptop GPU. The race must
never stutter.

## Budget

- Draw calls: keep the racing scene under ~150 draw calls. Use `InstancedMesh`
  (drei `<Instances>`) for repeated geometry (trees, rocks, crowd, curbs).
- Build kart and track meshes once; never allocate geometry/materials per frame.
- No `new` of THREE objects inside `useFrame`. Reuse scratch `Vector3`/`Quaternion`.
- Textures: KTX2/Basis compressed; geometry: Draco-compressed glTF.
- Use LOD (drei `<Detailed>`) for distant props.
- Shadows: one shadow-casting directional light; cap shadow map at 2048.
- Post FX kept cheap (bloom + light motion blur); gate heavy passes behind a quality
  setting and honor `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Pattern

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — allocates every frame
useFrame(() => { mesh.position.copy(new THREE.Vector3(x, 0.5, z)); });

// ✅ GOOD — reuse + read sim snapshot
const v = useMemo(() => new THREE.Vector3(), []);
useFrame(() => { mesh.position.set(state.x, 0.5, state.z); });
```

Rendering reads sim state; it never drives game logic.
